                            <comment id="13872150" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 15 Jan 2014 14:57:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That magic string looks very brittle to me - entries in zip files can come in any order&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would we not be better patching the &quot;container aware logic&quot; in ZipContainerDetector to check for the xps specific entries, so we have a solution that&apos;ll work no matter what order the files come in the zip structure?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13873175" author="101000" created="Thu, 16 Jan 2014 08:56:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with you but ... if you look at &quot;application/x-tika-ooxml&quot; in tika-mimetypes.xml you will find a similar approach (use of match and offset in zip files). &lt;br/&gt;
Anyways, are you thinking something like I porposed for DWFX files (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1204&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1204&lt;/a&gt;) ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13992908" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 8 May 2014 17:43:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;ZipContainerDetector support, additional MimeTypes details and a unit test added in r1593327.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
